26/05/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police on Tuesday (May 25th) arrested 45 people as part of a sweeping operation against organised crime. 
Among those detained is a customs officer from Montenegro who holds a Bosnian passport. 
In all, about 500 police officers raided 53 locations in both Republika Srpska and in the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina. 
(RTRS, Nezavisne Novine, RTS - 25/05/10)
